<p class="article-lead">The perfume manufacturing process begins before liquid enters a tank. Formula, components, artwork and acceptance criteria must be approved first; otherwise production only makes unresolved decisions harder to change.</p><ol><li><strong>Development:</strong> confirm fragrance direction, concentration and product format.</li><li><strong>Engineering:</strong> approve bottle, closure, decoration, carton and compatibility.</li><li><strong>Purchasing:</strong> order materials against controlled specifications and inspect receipt.</li><li><strong>Compounding:</strong> identify materials, weigh, mix and complete the defined resting or filtration steps.</li><li><strong>Filling and assembly:</strong> fill, close, code, decorate or label, box and pack.</li><li><strong>Release:</strong> inspect the liquid, function, appearance, quantities and records.</li></ol><p>A pre-production sample connects the separate approvals into one finished unit. Repeat orders should reference the same formula revision, component specifications, artwork and approved sample.</p>
